  "texts": [
    "As a result, the human author may not understand the chatbot's response at the first reading and refuse to interact with ChatGPT.",
    "He can also generate another story concept if he/she does not like the one offered.",
    "From the perspective of the future reader, the author has to choose carefully among the generated ideas and incorporate into the text only original ones to avoid falling into stereotypes and bore the reader.",
    "ChatGPT can also generate biased or unverified information.",
    "At the request to add an alternative world to the children's story, the chatbot produced a description that highly resembled the one in \"Alice in a Wonderland\" by Lewis Carroll (Figure 3)."
